  "texts": [
    "In contrast with foundational model's difficulties in answering in the required format, as it was not trained to understand instructions but simply to predict sequences of words.",
    "We focus on the network traffic under the format of flows, which are currently the most prominent and efficient source of network telemetry for threat detection due to their scalability [1].",
    "They summarise network traffic which shares destination and source port and IP addresses by aggregating packets into flows, making them ideal for detecting patterns indicative of malicious activities.",
    "Sarhan et al. [5] proposes a set of standardised Net-Flow datasets, with a common set of overlapping features, to address the limited ability to evaluate ML-based NIDS across different network environments and attack scenarios.",
    "Among these, we solely consider the datasets outside of the IoT domain: NF-UNSW-NB15-v2 and NF-CSE-CIC-IDS2018-v2."
  ],
